# lean-ctx Multi-Agent Orchestration (ModMe)

Complements [lean-ctx.mdc](./lean-ctx.mdc) for parallel worktrees and terminal orchestration.

## Protocol stack

Per [Which Protocol When](https://leanctx.com/docs/concepts/protocols/#which-protocol-when):

| Scenario | Protocols |
| Multi-agent parallel work | **CEP + CCP + A2A** |
| Single task with clear goal | **CLP** (ctx_preload when task is set) |

## Session start

1. `yarn agent:session:start` (or `.\scripts\agent-session-start.ps1`) — loads lean-ctx env + beads
2. `node scripts/lean-ctx-agent-catalog.mjs register --role dev` — A2A catalog snapshot
3. MCP: `ctx_agent` `register` (agent_type, role) + `ctx_preload` when task is clear
4. MCP: `ctx_session` `load` + `ctx_knowledge` `wakeup`
5. Optional: `-BootstrapIntelligence` → `.\scripts\lean-ctx-session-bootstrap.ps1` (graph + index + wakeup)

## Parallel dispatch

```powershell
yarn beads:bfs:dry          # inspect BFS layers before dispatch
yarn agent:session:start -TaskTitle "..." -ClaimPaths @("next-forge/apps/app/")
```

Use collection `role` fields from `scripts/collections/*.collection.json` and catalog `resolve --intent "..."`.

## Scent field (local A2A)

Buddy mode + scent CLAIM/DONE for path coordination — **no Remote Agent Bus** in Phase 1.

- Claim paths via `-ClaimPaths` on session start (agent-task-registry)
- Diary: `ctx_agent` `diary` category `progress` | `blocker` | `decision`

## Session end

1. MCP: `ctx_session` `save` + `ctx_knowledge` `consolidate`
2. `yarn agent:session:finish` — async telemetry (non-blocking `Start-Job`)
3. Optional: `.\scripts\lean-ctx-prove-it.ps1` for savings + scorecard

